"adj. 迷人的；友好的 【英】 adj.愉快的, 友好的(friendly, charming, and fashionably dressed) 【例】 He strolled about, looking very debonair in his elegant new suit. adj. 无忧无虑的; 和蔼而友好的 = charming = urbane = genial = jaunty 【记】deb = debt债务, on, air: 债务飞到天上去了, 不用还钱了! －无忧无虑的 【记】bon 好 + air空气，氛围 debonair (adj.)  c.1200, ""mild, gentle, kind courteous,"" from Old French debonaire, from de bon' aire ""of good race,"" originally used of hawks, hence, ""thoroughbred"" (opposite of French demalaire). Used in Middle English to mean ""docile, courteous,"" it became obsolete and was revived with an altered sense of ""pleasant, affable"" (1680s)."
